******
[1] I added (Mbarara)
Date: Sun 1 Mar 2009
Source: The New Vision (Uganda) [edited]
<http://www.newvision.co.ug/D/8/18/673098>


Mbarara fights banana wilt
--------------------------
The Mbarara agriculture and production department has launched a
campaign to control the banana bacterial wilt in the district. A team
headed by the district agricultural officer, Grace Byarugaba,
recently launched a task force for Nyamitanga division in Ruti. The
task force mobilises and sensitises the community on how to control the wilt.

Byarugaba said the disease had spread to all parts of the district
and it required a combined effort to control it. The disease has
forced farmers to sell off their plantations cheaply. Many farmers
have reportedly shifted to Mubende district.

Byarugaba advised farmers to the cut and bury the affected banana
plants. She added that the tools used for cutting the affected plants
must be washed in Jik [South African brand of household bleach] or
heated in fire to prevent the spread of the disease. "Farmers should
stop planting suckers for 3 months. Whoever wants to plant suckers
should first consult the task force committee. This will reduce the
spread," Byarugaba added

The LC5 [local council] vice-chairperson, Stephen Kamanyire, said 95
percent of Mbarara farmers depended on matooke [cooking bananas]. He
called for an emergency fund specifically for the banana bacterial
wilt from the National Agricultural Advisory Services (NAADS) to help
in the sensitisation of farmers.

[Byline: Fred Turyakira]

